{
  "stem": "21978.6",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Even when my misfortune was great, I was fortunate to be able to build my new life.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was fortunate in any-- many other ways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Being nurse, I have been able to help lot of people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I have been working for charities.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And being in our congregation, I work for mitzvah group.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I feel that my fortune is being able to do something for the others.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That was-- that's my fortune, that I can do something for the others.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The most important thing is not to be selfish, to tolerate others, to see the others.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not to love yourself like your-- your neighbor like you love yourself, but to tolerate your neighbors.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if you can't like your neighbors, just leave them alone.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And don't try to do always for yourself the better without, with, with, in, with, without regarding the others, and to think always about the others, not to be selfish.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For the young generation, to tolerate the others.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We are so mixed here in Australia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I consider myself Australian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I consider myself to, to try to do something for the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So maybe this little contribution, if I tell the young people that they should tolerate everybody who is here.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We are so mixed here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there are people who are of so many different backgrounds.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They should just try to understand them and not to try to push them aside to their way, but to understand their way of life.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And try to live, live together in harmony.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I think that I have said all of what I wanted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There might be things that I will remember later that I would have liked to say.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
